content.description: Start with both of your hands on the block that is down and to the right of the main face. Paste some awkward feet on, do a move up a jug, then climb up on jugs to the topout.
content.location: It is down and to the right of the main face.

content.description: Sit start on the left end of the right-trending arete up the side of the overhanging face. Climb up the rail, and top out when it runs out.
content.location: This is on the left side of the overhanging face.

content.description: Start with your left hand on a jug on the right side of the overhanging face and your right hand on the arete about a foot or two to the right of the jug. Put your feet on the block below, and bump up your hand along the smooth upper part directly above your head. For full value, don't use the holds out left.
content.location: It is on the right side of the overhanging face and slightly around the corner.

content.description: Start matched on an okay edge down low in the middle of the overhanging face, do a move up to the arete utilizing an intermediate crimp, then top out.
content.location: Sit start down low in the middle of the main face.

content.description: This is a small boulder located in front of and to the right of the first pulloff on Coolidge Street (if going north).
